4. Airports Domain

airports — id, iata_code (unique), icao_code, name, country_code, city, timezone, latitude, longitude, status (draft/active/inactive), is_featured, slug (unique), published_at, created_by, updated_by.
airport_translations — id, airport_id, locale (en/ar/...), short_description, full_description, arrival_instructions, departure_instructions, transit_instructions. Unique (airport_id, locale).
airport_images — id, airport_id, storage_key, alt_text, sort_order, is_primary.
airport_seo — id, airport_id, locale, meta_title, meta_description, focus_keywords, canonical_url, og_image_key, schema_json (jsonb), direct_answer_block, ai_summary. Unique (airport_id, locale).
airport_services — the join that makes a service available at an airport. id, airport_id, service_id, status (active/inactive), cut_off_minutes, min_notice_minutes, sort_order. Unique (airport_id, service_id). This row is the anchor for pricing, availability, and supplier coverage.

