7. Pricing Domain (supports D-008: fixed OR cost+markup, per row)

pricing_rules — id, airport_service_id, supplier_id (nullable — null = applies to the airport-service generally), mode (fixed | cost_plus_markup), base_price_minor (used when mode = fixed), supplier_cost_minor (used when mode = cost_plus_markup), markup_type (percentage | fixed_amount), markup_value, currency, passenger_pricing (jsonb: per-pax multipliers/tiers), peak_rules (jsonb), valid_from, valid_to, status, priority, created_by. Rule precedence: supplier-specific over general, higher priority over lower, narrower date range over wider.
currency_rates — id, base_currency, quote_currency, rate, fetched_at. Updated by a background job.
promo_codes — id, code (unique), discount_type (percentage/fixed), discount_value, currency, max_redemptions, redemptions_used, valid_from, valid_to, min_booking_minor, status, applicable_scope (jsonb: airports/services). Platform-funded in MVP (A-009).
promo_redemptions — id, promo_code_id, booking_id, discount_applied_minor, created_at.

The pricing engine reads these tables to produce a quote; the resulting numbers are then frozen into booking_price_snapshots (see Bookings).

