10. Bookings Domain

customers — id, email, phone, whatsapp, full_name, locale, is_vip, notes, created_at. Keyed by email/phone for history; no auth credentials in MVP (D-002). Deduplicated on email.
bookings — id, reference (unique, human-readable), customer_id, airport_service_id, supplier_id (nullable until assigned), status (enum, see lifecycle), direction (arrival/departure/transit), service_datetime (timestamptz), passenger_count, special_requests, locale, currency, total_minor, manage_token_hash, manage_token_expires_at, source (homepage/airport_page/...), created_at, updated_at.
booking_passengers — id, booking_id, full_name, type (adult/child/infant), notes.
booking_flights — id, booking_id, flight_number, airline_code, scheduled_time, terminal, gate, flight_status, last_synced_at.
booking_price_snapshots — id, booking_id, base_price_minor, supplier_cost_minor, markup_minor, passenger_adjustment_minor, peak_adjustment_minor, discount_minor, tax_estimate_minor, total_minor, margin_minor, currency, pricing_rule_id (reference only), promo_code_id (nullable), created_at. Immutable. This is the financial truth for the booking (D-004).
booking_status_history — id, booking_id, from_status, to_status, actor_type (system/staff/supplier/customer), actor_id, reason, created_at.
booking_supplier_assignments — id, booking_id, supplier_id, assigned_by, assignment_method (manual/rule_based), status (offered/accepted/rejected/reassigned), offered_at, responded_at, response_note. Full history of assignment attempts.
booking_notes — id, booking_id, author_user_id, body, visibility (internal/customer), created_at.
booking_events — id, booking_id, type, payload (jsonb), created_at. The timeline feed (created, paid, supplier assigned, confirmed, flight delay detected, incident, completed, refunded...).

Booking lifecycle statuses: Draft · Pending Payment · Paid · Pending Supplier Assignment · Supplier Assigned · Pending Supplier Confirmation · Confirmed · In Progress · Completed · Cancelled · Refunded · Failed/Incident. Because the customer is charged at checkout (D-007), the normal path is Pending Payment → Paid → Pending Supplier Assignment with no auth-hold state.

