11. Payments & Settlements Domain (D-006 merchant of record)

payments — id, booking_id, stripe_payment_intent_id (unique), amount_minor, currency, status (requires_payment/processing/succeeded/failed/refunded/partially_refunded), payment_method_type, captured_at, created_at.
payment_transactions — id, payment_id, type (charge/refund/adjustment), amount_minor, currency, stripe_object_id, created_at. Append-only ledger.
stripe_webhook_events — id, stripe_event_id (unique), type, payload (jsonb), processing_status (received/processed/failed), processed_at, error. Ensures idempotency; every webhook persisted before processing.
settlements — id, supplier_id, period_start, period_end, status (draft/approved/paid), gross_minor, deductions_minor, net_payable_minor, currency, approved_by, paid_at.
settlement_lines — id, settlement_id, booking_id, supplier_cost_minor, refund_adjustment_minor, penalty_minor, net_minor. Links each booking's supplier cost into a payout.
payouts — id, settlement_id, amount_minor, currency, method, external_reference, status, paid_at.

