21. Indexing Strategy

- Unique: airports.iata_code, airports.slug, services.slug, pages.slug, bookings.reference, payments.stripe_payment_intent_id, stripe_webhook_events.stripe_event_id, promo_codes.code.
- Composite: airport_services(airport_id, service_id); *_translations(parent_id, locale); supplier_coverage(supplier_id, airport_service_id); pricing_rules(airport_service_id, status, priority).
- Search/filter: bookings(status, service_datetime), bookings(customer_id), incidents(status, severity), notification_queue(status, next_attempt_at), flight_monitor_jobs(status, last_checked_at).
- Every foreign key column is indexed.
- GIN indexes on full-text search columns (airport/service names + translations) and on jsonb columns queried by key.

⸻

22. Data Integrity Rules

- Foreign keys enforced everywhere; ON DELETE RESTRICT for financial/booking data, ON DELETE CASCADE only for pure child content (e.g. translations, images).
- booking_price_snapshots, payment_transactions, stripe_webhook_events, audit_logs, ai_generation_logs are append-only — no updates, no deletes.
- Money columns are NOT NULL with a currency companion column; CHECK constraints ensure non-negative where appropriate.
- Status transitions enforced in the service layer and recorded in the relevant *_history table; the DB stores current status, history stores the path.
- Soft delete (deleted_at) for airports, services, suppliers, pages; hard delete forbidden for anything financial or booking-linked.

⸻

23. Migration & Seeding

- Prisma Migrate; every migration reviewed and reversible where possible.
- Seed data: roles, permissions, role_permissions, the three MVP services, default settings, notification_templates, cancellation_policies (global default), ai_prompt_templates. No seeded airports or prices (D: nothing hardcoded).
- Environments: development, staging, production — each with its own database; staging mirrors production schema.

